-- Network Rail Said to Plan Sale of Index-Linked Bonds in Pounds
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-02-29T12:26:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/network-rail-said-to-plan-sale-of-index-linked-bonds-in-pounds.html
Network Rail Infrastructure Finance
Plc plans to sell inflation-linked bonds in pounds, according to
a banker with knowledge in the transaction.  Bank of America Corp. and Deutsche Bank AG are managing the
issuance, which will include taps of existing inflation-linked
securities, the banker said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah Benjamin in London at 
